---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const cityLinks = [
  { name: 'Orem, UT', href: '/service-areas/orem-ut', desc: 'Home base. Fastest response times, full residential and commercial services.' },
  { name: 'Springville, UT', href: '/service-areas/springville-ut', desc: 'Driveway and parking lot paving for Art City neighborhoods.' },
  { name: 'Spanish Fork, UT', href: '/service-areas/spanish-fork-ut', desc: 'Asphalt repair and new paving for the east bench and canyon-adjacent subdivisions.' },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What parts of Utah County do you cover?', a: 'We work throughout the valley floor from Santaquin and Payson in the south, through Springville, Provo, and Orem, up to Lehi and American Fork in the north. If you\'re outside that range, text us and we\'ll tell you honestly whether we can get to you.' },
  { q: 'Is Utah County asphalt different from other regions?', a: 'The valley floor near Utah Lake tends to have heavier, clay-rich soil that drains poorly, which means sub-base prep matters more here than in areas with rockier ground closer to the benches. Combine that with Utah\'s freeze-thaw winters and hot, dry summers, and it\'s a demanding climate for asphalt that isn\'t installed correctly the first time.' },
  { q: 'Do you work with HOAs and commercial properties countywide?', a: 'Yes. Alongside residential driveways, we handle HOA common areas, church parking lots, and commercial lots for businesses throughout Utah County.' },
  { q: 'How do I know if I need a new company or just a repair?', a: 'It depends on the extent of the damage. Surface cracking and small potholes are usually repairable. Widespread alligator cracking, sinking, or a base that\'s failed usually means it\'s time for full replacement. We\'ll give you an honest read during your free quote, not just a sales pitch.' },
  { q: 'Is there a paving season in Utah County?', a: 'Asphalt needs adequate ambient and ground temperature to compact and cure properly, so most new paving and major replacement work happens spring through fall. Crack sealing and smaller repairs can often be scheduled outside that window.' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Utah County Asphalt Paving Contractor | J&C Asphalt"
  description="J&C Asphalt is a Utah County asphalt paving contractor serving residential driveways and commercial parking lots from Santaquin to Lehi. Free quotes."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Utah County, UT</span>
      <h1 class="section-title">Utah County Asphalt Paving Contractor</h1>
      <p>Utah County is one of the fastest-growing counties in the country, stretching from Santaquin and Payson in the south, through the Provo-Orem urban core, up through Lehi and American Fork's Silicon Slopes tech corridor in the north. J&amp;C Asphalt is a Utah County asphalt company built for that range, handling everything from single driveways in established neighborhoods to commercial lots for growing businesses.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
        <a href="/work" class="btn-outline">See Our Work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="area-overview">
        <div class="area-image">
          <img
            src="/images/aerial-1.jpg"
            alt="Aerial view of J&C Asphalt paving crew working on a Utah County project"
            width="640"
            height="520"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="area-text">
          <span class="section-label">Countywide Coverage</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Built for Utah County's Terrain and Climate</h2>
          <p>Utah County sits in a bowl formed by the Wasatch Range and Mt. Timpanogos to the east, Utah Lake at its center, and the Traverse Mountains separating it from Salt Lake Valley to the north. That geography creates real variation in ground conditions: heavier, clay-rich soil near the lake that holds water and needs proper sub-base prep, versus rockier, better-draining ground on the benches closer to the mountains.</p>
          <p>On top of that, Utah's climate puts real stress on asphalt everywhere in the county: freeze-thaw cycling through the winter that works its way into small cracks and widens them, and long, hot, dry summers that push oxidation and surface wear. A driveway or lot that's installed without accounting for both will fail faster than one that is.</p>
          <p>We build every project, residential or commercial, around the specific ground and drainage conditions of the site, not a one-size-fits-all approach.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Countywide Perspective</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Three Different Parts of Utah County</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="neighborhoods-text">
        <p>The north end of the county, Lehi, American Fork, and Pleasant Grove, has grown fastest over the last decade thanks to the Silicon Slopes tech corridor and the new subdivisions built to house it. Most of the paving work up there is new installation on recently graded lots and commercial parking for growing office campuses.</p>
        <p>The central corridor, Provo and Orem, is older and more built out, with Utah Valley University and Brigham Young University anchoring dense residential neighborhoods that date back decades. That's where we see the most driveway replacement work, older asphalt that's simply reached the end of its life.</p>
        <p>The south end, Springville, Spanish Fork, Payson, and Santaquin, is a mix of older town centers and land that's transitioning from agricultural use to residential subdivisions as the valley continues to grow south. That mix means both repair work on established streets and new paving as farmland gets built out.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Explore by City</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Utah County Service Areas</h2>
        <p class="section-sub">We serve every city in the valley. Here's a closer look at a few of our core markets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="city-link-grid">
        {cityLinks.map(city => (
          <a href={city.href} class="city-link-card">
            <h3>{city.name}</h3>
            <p>{city.desc}</p>
            <span class="card-link">View Area &rarr;</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <a href="/service-areas" class="btn-outline-red">See All Service Areas &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Common Questions</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Utah County Asphalt FAQ</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-grid">
        {faqs.map(item => (
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>{item.q}</h3>
            <p>{item.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="area-bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Get a Quote?</h2>
      <p>Tell us your city and project details and we'll get back to you, usually within 24 hours.</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
        <a href="sms:+13854409882" class="btn-outline-red">Text (385) 440-9882</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .page-hero p { color: #666; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; max-width: 720px; }

  .section-pad { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .section-dark { background-color: #F2F5F2; }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  }

  .section-sub {
    color: #666;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .area-overview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .area-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 520px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
  }

  .area-text h2 { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .area-text p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .neighborhoods-text {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .neighborhoods-text p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }

  .city-link-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .city-link-card {
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #C8CEC8;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .city-link-card:hover {
    border-color: #cd553f;
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  .city-link-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #121212;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .city-link-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-link {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #cd553f;
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #C8CEC8;
    border-left: 3px solid #cd553f;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: #121212;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta {
    background-color: #cd553f;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta h2 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .area-bottom-cta p {
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 520px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .area-bottom-cta .btn-outline-red { border-color: #000; color: #000; }
  .area-bottom-cta .btn-outline-red:hover { background-color: #000; color: #cd553f; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .area-overview { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .city-link-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .faq-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 580px) {
    .city-link-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
